Title: Broccoli Cheddar Egg Muffins
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 cup broccoli, chopped

  • 1/4 cup diced onion

  • 5 slices of turkey bacon

  • 8 eggs

  • 1/2 cup low fat shredded cheese

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • 1/2 tsp garlic powder

  • 1/4 tsp salt

  • 1/4 tsp pepper

Directions:

  1. Preheat the oven to 400°F.

  2. Cook turkey bacon according to package instructions and then cut up into small pieces.

  3. Add olive oil, broccoli, onion, salt, garlic powder, and pepper to a pan and sauté over medium heat.

  4. In a bowl, whisk the eggs, bacon, and cheese.

  5. Pour pan contents into the bowl and mix throughly.

  6. In a six count muffin tin, distribute mix evenly and bake for 15-20 minutes or until completely cooked.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 4 servings

1 muffin (114g): 159 calories, 10 g fat, 4 g carbohydrates, 12g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Broccoli Cheddar Egg Muffins

#breakfast #recipes #easy #mealprep #lowcarb #eggs #brunch

Title: Tater Tot Breakfast Casserole
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb. turkey sausage

  • 1.5 cups egg whites

  • 1.5 cup low fat cottage cheese

  • 6 servings of tater tots (504 g)

  • 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese

  • 1/2 tsp salt

  • 1/2 tsp pepper

  • 1/2 tsp garlic powder

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 375°F degrees.

  2. Spray a casserole dish with cooking grease and set aside.

  3. Heat a skillet over medium-high heat.

  4. Brown turkey sausage and drain excess grease from skillet. Set aside.

  5. In a blender, add egg whites, cottage cheese, and seasonings. Blend until creamy.

  6. Pour the blended egg mixture into the bottom of the greased casserole dish and add the cooked turkey sausage.

  7. Sprinkle ½ of the cheese across the top.

  8. Evenly distribute the tater tots across the top of the casserole and add the remaining cheese.

  9. Bake at 375°F for 40 mins.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving (270g): 435 calories, 22g fat, 29g carbohydrates, 31g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Tater Tot Breakfast Casserole

#breakfast #recipes #easy #mealprep #casserole #brunch

Title: Shrimp and Broccoli Stir Fry
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb. shrimp, peeled and deveined

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

  • 2 tbsp agave or honey

  • 2 tbsp reduced sodium soy sauce

  • 1/2 tsp ginger

  • 1 tbsp minced garlic

  • 2 cups broccoli

  • 2 cups brown rice

Directions:

  1. In a bowl, mix olive oil, agave, soy sauce, ginger, and minced garlic.

  2. Marinade shrimp in the sauce for 20 minutes.

  3. Steam broccoli and cook rice, set both aside.

  4. In a large skillet on medium high heat, pour shrimp and sauce into pan and sear for 2 minutes on each side.

  5. Add broccoli and rice and reduce heat to low.

  6. Cover and let sear for 5 minutes or until all sauce has been absorbed.

  7. Enjoy!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving (209g): 259 calories, 7g fat, 28g carbohydrates, 21g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Shrimp and Broccoli Stir Fry

#dinner #recipes #shrimp #stirfry #seafood

Title: Cheeseburger Wrap
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb. 90% lean ground beef

  • 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce

  • 2 tbsp sugar free ketchup

  • 2 tbsp mustard

  • 1 tsp minced onion

  • 1 dash of salt and pepper

  3. Lay Lavash bread sheets flat and sprinkle cheese on each.

  4. Add beef, lettuce, and tomato to Lavash bread.

Title: Creamy Butternut Squash Pasta
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 cups butternut squash

  • 3 tbsp olive oil

  • 1/4 tsp salt

  • 1/4 tsp black pepper

  • 1/2 lb. turkey sausage, crumbled

  • 4 garlic cloves, minced

  • 6 oz. spinach

  • 1 cup heavy cream

  • 1/3 cup shredded parmesan cheese

  • 8 oz. Banza bow tie pasta

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400°F.

  2. In a large bowl, toss cubed butternut squash with 1 tbsp olive oil, salt, and pepper.

  3. Spread the squash on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet in one layer and roast for 30 minutes.

  4. In a medium skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil on medium heat.

  5. Add crumbled sausage to skillet and cook for about 10 minutes, regularly stirring, until the sausage is cooked through. Set aside.

  6. Cook pasta according to package instructions. Set aside.

  7. In a separate, large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil together with minced garlic and spinach over medium heat and cook for about 5 or 7 minutes or until spinach starts to wilt.

  8. Add heavy cream to skillet until boiling, then immediately reduce to simmer.

  9. Add shredded Parmesan cheese to skillet continuing to stir on simmer until the cheese melts.

  10. Add cooked, drained pasta, cooked sausage, and butternut squash to the skillet with the creamy spinach sauce and stir to combine.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 8 servings

1 serving (176g): 366 calories, 23g fat, 24g carbohydrates, 19g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Creamy Butternut Squash Pasta

#dinner #recipes #easy #pasta #squash

Title: Foil Baked Salmon and Asparagus
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 salmon fillet (around 1 lb)

  • 2 tbsps reduced sodium bone broth

  • 2 tsp minced garlic

  • 1.5 tbsp lemon juice

  • ½ tsp salt

  • ½ tsp pepper

  • 2 tbsp avocado oil butter

  • 2 tbsp parsley

  • 1 lb asparagus (450 g)

Directions:

  1. Preheat your oven to 425℉.

  2. Prepare 2 aluminum foil sheets (14 x 12) on top of a baking sheet.

  3. In a small mixing bowl, combine bone broth, lemon juice, garlic, butter, salt, and pepper.

  4. Lay salmon on one sheet of foil and fold edges up so that the salmon is surrounded and the mixture won’t fall out.

  5. Lay asparagus on the other sheet of foil. Spray both with cooking spray. Pour ¾ of sauce mixture on the salmon and the remaining ¼ on the asparagus.

  6. Add parsley on top of both asparagus and salmon

  7. Cook for 20-25 minutes or until salmon is cooked all the way through.

  8. Carefully unwrap each sheet of foil and let cool before eating.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 4 servings

1 serving (259g): 290 calories, 15g fat, 6g carbohydrates, 32g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Foil Baked Salmon and Asparagus

#dinner #recipes #easy #salmon #omega3s

Title: Sweet Potato Hash
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 medium sweet potatoes, cut into cubes (3 cups)

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

  • ½ tsp ground cumin

  • ½ tsp chili powder

  • ¼ tsp sea salt

  • 1 can of black beans, drained and rinsed

  • 2 tsp lime juice

  • 1 tsp pepper

  • ¼ cup chopped cilantro

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400℉.

  2. Prepare a baking sheet.

  3. In a large bowl, add 1 tbsp olive oil, cumin, chili powder, and salt. Mix. Add in sweet potatoes and toss until they are coated.

  4. Place sweet potatoes on the baking sheet and bake for 25 minutes or until tender.

  5. When the sweet potatoes have 5 minutes remaining, add black beans, 1 tsp lime juice, and 1 tbsp olive oil to a medium sized skillet. Mix and let saute for 5 minutes.

  6. Add sweet potatoes and other tsp of lime juice to the skillet. Stir to combine. Add cilantro on top.

  7. Let it heat for 3 more minutes and enjoy!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving (213g): 245 calories, 6g fat, 42g carbohydrates, 8g protein, 12g fiber

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Sweet Potato Hash

Title: Black Beans and Rice
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 cups brown rice

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • ½ cup diced onion

  • 1 medium diced bell pepper

  • 1 ½ tsp minced garlic

  • 3 cups reduced-sodium bone broth

  • 1 can diced tomatoes

  • 1 tbsp fresh chopped cilantro

  • 2 tsp ground cumin

  • 1 tsp chili powder

  • ¼ tsp sea salt

  • 2 can black beans, drained and rinsed

  • 2 tbsp lime juice

Directions:

  1. Cook brown rice according to the package instructions.

  2. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet. Once oil is hot, add the onions, bell pepper, and garlic. Saute for 5 minutes.

  3. Add bone broth, cooked brown rice, beans, tomatoes, cilantro, cumin, chili powder, oregano, and salt to skillet. Stir.

  4. Bring to a boil on high heat then cover with the lid and reduce to simmer on medium low heat. Simmer for about 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

  5. Stir in lime juice and let sit for 5 minutes.

  6. Serve and enjoy.

Nutrition Data:

Title: Healthy Cinnamon Apples
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 3 apples (about 3 cups, chopped)

  • 2 tbsp water

  • 1 tbsp coconut oil

  • 1 tbsp honey (sub maple syrup)

  • ½ tsp ground cinnamon

  • ⅛ tsp sea salt

  • ¼ tsp pure vanilla extract

Directions:

  1. Cut apples into cubes.

  2. Place apples pieces into a skillet with 2 tbsp water. Cover the pan and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the apples become slightly soft and water is absorbed.

  3. Add coconut oil to the skillet. Stir apples and oil together until all the apples are coated. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring every minute or so, until the apples become soft (If apples do not soften, cover apples for the last 2 minutes).

  4. Add honey (or maple syrup), cinnamon, salt, and vanilla to apple mixture. Stir until well mixed.

  5. Cook for about 5 more minutes, stirring every minute until the apples reach your desired softness!

Title: Healthier Baked Ziti
Description:

  • 8 oz ziti noodles (100% whole wheat)

  • 1.5 lbs. ground beef

  • 3 cups Primal Kitchen Marinara sauce

  • 1/2 cup cottage cheese (low fat)

  • 4 oz reduced fat mozzarella cheese

  • 1 egg

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • 1 tbsp Italian seasoning

  • 1 tsp minced garlic, salt, and pepper

Directions:

  1. Cook pasta according to package directions.

  2. While pasta is cooking, heat olive oil in a skillet.

  3. Add garlic and sauté for 1 minute.

  4. Add ground beef and seasonings to skillet and cook until done.

  5. Pre-heat oven to 375 and spray a casserole dish with cooking spray.

  6. In a large mixing bowl, add ground beef, pasta, 2 cups marinara, half of the mozzarella, cottage cheese, and egg.

  7. Add ½ cup of marinara to the bottom of the casserole dish and spread with a spoon.

  8. Then, add in the contents of the mixing bowl to dish.

  9. Top dish with another ½ cup of marinara and remaining cheese.

  10. Bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Sweet Potato Nachos
Description:
Ingredients

  • 2 large sweet potatoes

  • 1 lb 95% lean ground beef

  • 1 pack of taco seasoning

  • 2 oz low fat cheese (dairy free or regular)

  • 1 c chopped peppers

  • ½ chopped white onion + 1 TBSP olive oil to cook (optional)

    Toppings

  • 1 avocado (diced)

  • ½ c shredded lettuce

    Instructions:
    1. Slice sweet potatoes into thin rounds and place evenly on baking sheet.
    2. Cook sweet potatoes for 25-30 minutes (or until browned) at 400 degrees F.
    3. While sweet potatoes are in oven, (add olive oil and onion to skillet), then add ground beef into onions to cook. Season with taco seasoning of choice
    4. Take sweet potato out of oven.
    5. Spread ground beef, cheese, and peppers evenly over sweet potato thins.
    6. Cook in oven for 5 additional minutes to melt cheese.
    7. Take out of oven and add into serving dishes.
    8. Top with diced avocado and lettuce.

    For individuals with IBS, omit onions and choose a taco seasoning without onion or garlic powder. Low amounts of red, yellow, and orange bell peppers are generally low FODMAP. Choose green bell peppers in larger amounts for a low FODMAP choice as well.

Nutrition Data:

Total Servings: 4

1 serving (1 protein ball): 461 calories, 19g fat, 34g carbohydrates, 38g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Sweet Potato Nachos

Title: Roasted Sausage & Veggie Medley
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 pack (1lb) Aidell’s chicken apple sausage (or your favorite sausage), cut into 1-inch rounds

  • 1 lb Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved

  • 2 sweet potatoes, cubed

  • 1 honey crisp apple, diced

For the Marinade:

  • 3 Tbsp olive oil

  • ¼ cup coconut aminos

  • 1 tbsp Dijon mustard

  • 1 tsp onion powder

  • ½ tsp garlic powder

  • ½ tsp paprika

  • ½ tsp sea salt

Directions:

  1. Preheat your oven to 425°F and line a large baking sheet.

  2. Spread the Brussels sprouts, sweet potatoes, honey crisp apple, and chicken apple sausage on the pan in a single layer.

  3. Whisk together the marinade ingredients, then pour over the veggie and sausage mix.

  4. Use your hands to mix well and coat everything evenly.

  5. Roast mixture in a single layer for 20 minutes, tossing halfway through, until everything is browned and tender.

  6. Enjoy!

Title: Homemade Peanut Butter Cups
Description:
Ingredients:

For chocolate

  • 1 cup dark chocolate

  • 1 tsp coconut oil

For filling

  • 1/4 c natural PB

  • 1/4 c oat flour

  • 1 tsp vanilla

  • 1 TBSP maple syrup

Directions:

  1. Pour dark chocolate and coconut oil in a microwave safe bowl.

  2. Microwave in 15-30 second increments, stirring between each, until chocolate is fully melted.

  3. Fill mold approximately 1/3 of volume with dark chocolate.

  4. Freeze 10-15 minutes or until chocolate layer is completely hardened.

  5. While chocolate is in freezer, mix PB, oat flour, vanilla, and maple syrup in a separate bowl until a thick dough like consistency.

  6. Take mold out of freezer, add a small portion of filling into each mold, pressing filling into the mold with your finger so that it is flat on top of the chocolate layer.

  7. Cover PB layer with melted chocolate in each mold.

  8. Freeze for 10-15 minutes or until chocolate is completely hardened.

  9. One by one, carefully pop each PB “cup” out of the mold and enjoy!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 18 servings

1 serving (1 PB cup or 16g): 89 calories, 6g fat, 7g carbohydrates, 2g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Homemade Peanut Butter Cups

Title: Snow Globe Mocktail
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 rosemary leaf

  • Approx. 1/2 c or 1 handful of whole cranberries

  • water

  • Probiotic soda or beverage of choice

Directions:

  • Prepare the Glass:

    • Take one glasses and place a small handful of cranberries at the bottom.

  • Prepare the Rosemary:

    • Take a sprig of rosemary, turn it upside down, and trim the bottom so it’s even.

    • Spread out the bottom leaves slightly to help it stand upright in the glass.

  • Assemble the Glass:

    • Place the rosemary sprig into the middle of the glass.

    • Pour water into the glass, covering the cranberries and stabilizing the rosemary. Alternatively, pour water first, then position the rosemary sprig so it stays upright.

  • Freeze:

    • Set the glass on a small baking sheet for stability and place in the freezer.

    • Freeze for about 45 minutes, or until the water is completely frozen.

  • Serve:

    • Remove the glass from the freezer and serve immediately.

    • Pour your favorite sparkling water or probiotic drink over the frozen setup for a magical "snow globe" effect. Cronometer recipe uses a Cran fizz Poppi.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 2 serving

1 drink: 36 calories, 0 g fat, 9 g carbohydrates, 0 g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Snow Globe Mocktail
